
// The code snippet demonstrates the use of the [add] slot to append nodes from the [args] section of a [sockets.signal] invocation to the current node set. It retrieves nodes specified in the [.arguments] node using the [get-nodes] slot and adds them to the [args] node, effectively merging argument data into the signal's arguments.
add:x:./*/sockets.signal/*/args
   get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*
